reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars FUNYET gave no Windows product key
reviews.reviewText: Ladies and gents, saddle up because today has been an emotional ride. I bought this laptop with the intent to use it for work. I need to be able to access 9 websites, check my email, and run numbers. Pretty simple stuff that I’m after. It arrived today. Unoboxing was painfully simple. The user manual is all but useless, in my humble opinion. There were multiple updates to be had.. which is to be expected as I can only assume the computer is actually a couple of years old despite this being its first use outside of the quality control diagnostics. Y’all. I was on Amazon chat for an hour and a half, 6 different agents, and no assistance in my issue. This is advertised as included with Windows 11 Pro. I had to call Microsoft and be walked through how to locate the key associated with the device only to discover my product key had already be used on a DIFFERENT DEVICE and was no longer available for my use, despite my paying for it. My new laptop wanted me to pay for a $200+ licensed product key despite it being sold to me with 11 Pro included. I got lucky and the rep with Microsoft support was able to get my Windows activated.Please read and learn from my misfortune.Aside from that huge hiccup upon receiving and set up, I’m now logged into all of my accounts and am very excited to have a computer that I’ve never written a high school essay on. Note there is no Ethernet access, no CD/DVD ROM, nor does it have a full sized HDMI port. These aren’t deal breakers for me simply because this computer was bought for work purposes opposed to personal.I’m very impressed by how light it is, the backlit keyboard, the fingerprint sensor, number pad, and the screen quality. For the price, this full sized laptop didn’t skimp on user friendly design features.Computer itself: 9/10Setup: 0/10Amazon Support: everyone but Mustafa(10), 0/10Microsoft Support: 11/10*Updated Review*Since receiving contact from the company in question, I’d like to state I’m please with their customer service and support. They reached out and were willing to right their wrongs. Upon reflection, I have updated my review as my laptop functions above expectation and allows me to do everything I require for my work and it was also reasonably priced considering its features.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It’s pretty good!
reviews.reviewText: I love the quality of this laptop so much the screen quality and it works super fast! The laptop is nice and big and it’s nothing like the super slow laptops that take 20 years to load and log you in. Some of the things that make it a four star not a five star is that if you want to use it for longer periods of time you need to have it plugged in the whole time because the battery life is at most like 2.5-3 hours which isn’t as good compared to other laptops that have some battery life’s lasting almost 7-8 hours. The battery save helps a little bit but it doesn’t do as much as you think. The next thing that I don’t like is that when the computer dies or you shut it down the updates take a lot of time even getting to almost 45 minutes and that’s might not seem to bad but for kids that takes quite a bit. Overall this laptop was very nice and it’s pretty good but some of the little things need a bit of tweaking but other than that it’s a pretty good product
